    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s bond yields steady; rupee guidance peg appreciates by 7 cents",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka treasury bill and bonds market remained dull on Monday (15) with only a handful of maturities quoted while the guidance peg on interbank spot trading strengthened by seven cents, dealers said.",
        "\u201cThe market is still waiting for debt restructuring clarifications,\u201d a market dealer said.",
        "Only a handful of maturities were active in the first few hours of trade.",
        "A bond maturing on 01. 06. 2025 was quoted at 27.15/28.15 percent on Monday, easing from 27.30/28.30 percent on Friday.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank announced guidance peg for interbank transactions strengthened by 07 cents to 360.92 rupees against the US dollar on Monday from 360.85 rupees.",
        "Data showed that commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers between 369.70 and 370.00 for small transactions. (Colombo/ Aug 15/2022)"
      ],
